-- 002 : basic lexer view --

in this documentation we will explore the lexer of xiat programming language
with is suprisely simple, in (IT-2 VER) the tokens are following:
(type, value) with exeptions of whitespaces and @ (comment)

-- token types --
the following token types and their respetive value
('BLOCKOPEN', \( or \[ or \{)
('BLOCKCLOSE', \) or \] or \})
('COMM', . or ,)
('SEMI', ;)
('SIGN', =)
('VARPTR', $)
('PLUS', +)
('SUBT', -)
('ASTE', *)
('SLASH', /)
('RIGHT', >)
('LEFT', <)
('CH', anything else)
('STRLIT', \"*\")
('ALNUM', 0-9 a-z A-Z)

-- how does it tokenize --
this information might be important to understanding the language
it separates tokens from each category:
whitespace / commnets (ignores)
single character tokens (+-/*><;.,)
multi character tokens ("hello world", 69420, funny60inmy09)
this dont invalide any tokens (even invalid like # : or ðŸŽˆ)

(001 - start point) < . > (003 - basic parser view)
